import React, { useState } from 'react'; import Navbar from '../components/Navbar'; import './SalaryTracker.css'; const SalaryTracker = ({ user, onLogout }) => { const [year, setYear] = useState('2024'); const [salaryData] = useState([ { id: 'E001', name: 'John Smith', baseSalary: 50000, bonus: 5000, deduction: 2000, netSalary: 53000 }, { id: 'E002', name: 'Sarah Johnson', baseSalary: 55000, bonus: 6000, deduction: 2500, netSalary: 58500 }, { id: 'E003', name: 'Mike Davis', baseSalary: 48000, bonus: 4500, deduction: 1800, netSalary: 50700 }, { id: 'E004', name: 'Emily Brown', baseSalary: 52000, bonus: 5500, deduction: 2200, netSalary: 55300 }, { id: 'E005', name: 'Robert Wilson', baseSalary: 60000, bonus: 7000, deduction: 3000, netSalary: 64000 }, ]); const totalBaseSalary = salaryData.reduce((sum, emp) => sum + emp.baseSalary, 0); const totalBonus = salaryData.reduce((sum, emp) => sum + emp.bonus, 0); const totalNetSalary = salaryData.reduce((sum, emp) => sum + emp.netSalary, 0); return (

Employee Salary Tracker

Total Base Salary ${(totalBaseSalary / 1000).toFixed(0)}K
Total Bonus ${(totalBonus / 1000).toFixed(0)}K
Total Net Salary ${(totalNetSalary / 1000).toFixed(0)}K
{salaryData.map((employee) => ( ))}
Employee ID Employee Name Base Salary Bonus Deduction Net Salary Action
{employee.id} {employee.name} ${employee.baseSalary.toLocaleString()} ${employee.bonus.toLocaleString()} ${employee.deduction.toLocaleString()} ${employee.netSalary.toLocaleString()}
); }; export default SalaryTracker;
